<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Tree or more commonly shrub to 7 m, variable in habit, with arching branches, often near leafless when flowering, stems glabrous, bark light brown, latex present, white. Leaves petiolate, 4-10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.3-6 cm, ovate, finely acuminate and mucronate, truncate to very shallowly cordate, glabrous; petioles 1.5-5 cm. Inflorescence of shortly pedunculate, 1-3-flowered cymes often borne on small axillary side branches; peduncles 0.2-3 cm; bracteoles 3 mm, oblong, caducous; pedicels 20-32 mm, thickened upwards; sepals subequal, abaxially glabrous, adaxially pubescent, the margins scarious, outer 9-11 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-8 mm, oblong-ovate, acute, often mucronate, inner sepals similar but scarious margins broader; corolla 5-7.5 cm long, white, broadly funnel-shaped, glabrous, tube commonly reddish inside, limb 7 cm diam., undulate; stamens 9-12 mm long; stigmas cylindrical, c. 2.5 mm long. Capsules 18-22 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10-12 mm, ellipsoid glabrous; seeds 10-11 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5 mm, glabrous apart from the pilose margins, the hairs white c. 9-12 mm long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
